  "id": "boss_quadratic_equations_v1",
  "task_description": "Part A — Algebraic:\n  Solve x² − 5x + 6 = 0.\n  (1) Solve by factoring — find the factored form and state both roots.\n  (2) Confirm both roots using the quadratic formula. Show the discriminant calculation separately.\n  (3) Verify each root by substituting into the original equation.\n\nPart B — Word Problem (Law 6 sensor):\n  A rectangular garden has a length that is 3 meters more than its width. The area is 40 square meters.\n  (1) Define your variable. Write an equation for the area.\n  (2) Rearrange into standard form ax² + bx + c = 0 and solve.\n  (3) State which solution is valid in context and explain why.\n",
  "sensor_purpose": "Part A is the Laws 1+2+3+4 integration test. x = 2 and x = 3 are close enough that lucky guessing can produce one root; the discriminant (b²−4ac = 1) shown separately and dual substitution verification in step (3) rule this out. Part B is the terminal Law 6 sensor. Two canonical transcription failures: writing w + (w+3) = 40 (confusing area with perimeter) or w·3 = 40 (ignoring width as a factor). The correct equation w(w+3) = 40 rearranges to w² + 3w − 40 = 0, giving (w+8)(w−5) = 0. Rejecting w = −8 as non-physical completes the Law 6 contextual reasoning. All 6 laws are exercised in adjacent parts of the same problem.\n",
