 "unit": "7 — Quadratic Functions & Equations",
 "description": "The student can find the axis of symmetry (x = −b/2a), vertex, and x-intercepts of a quadratic in standard form y = ax² + bx + c, determine whether the parabola opens upward or downward, and identify the minimum or maximum. Law 5 in the quadratic context: the parabola is a U-shaped dynamic relationship where the vertex is the turning point and the axis of symmetry is the balance line. The direction of opening depends on the sign of a — the leading coefficient is the engine of the relationship's shape.\n",
