 "unit": "7 — Quadratic Functions & Equations",
 "description": "The student can solve a quadratic equation ax² + bx + c = 0 by factoring and confirm the roots using the quadratic formula. They can also translate a real-world quadratic constraint from a word problem into a correctly structured equation before solving. This artifact activates all six diagnostic laws simultaneously: balance (Law 1), inverse operations (Law 2), identity-based roots (Law 3), structural factoring (Law 4), the dynamic two-variable relationship (Law 5), and real-world transcription (Law 6). The full-sensor artifact — the terminal diagnostic gate of the curriculum.\n",
 "unlock_condition": "mastery >= 0.8 on all required skills, confirmed by boss challenge",
 "mastery_threshold": 0.8,
 "skills_required": [
